abstract: Australia defeats South Africa, 11-9, in Rugby World Cup quarterfinals; Australia will face New Zealand in semifinals.
snippet: James O’Connor scored on a penalty in the 72nd minute and Australia rallied to beat defending champion South Africa, 11-9, in a Rugby World Cup quarterfinal in Wellington, New Zealand.
